review.reviewBody: You can definitely taste the fresh, quality ingredients they use here! Have had the A+ Croissanwich multiple times and never lets me down. The Walnut Chocolate Chip Drop Cookie is normally always a delight, except this time mine was burnt. :( Nearly black on the bottom, hard burnt edges, dry and not nearly as chewy as it normally is. Will continue to order from here but hoping their best-selling cookie will be in better shape next time!
Egg was not perfectly runny, it was RAW! The hollandaise is also gross, like margarine? Just really awful. How do you mess up an Eggs Benny?

If you're considering dining here, be prepared for very small portions. While the food quality might be good, the serving sizes are disappointingly small. You might find yourself still hungry after a meal, especially if you have a larger appetite. This place might be more suitable for a light snack rather than a full meal. The flavors are enjoyable, but the portion sizes leave much to be desired.
Excellent store with quality coffee and sandwiches. Best coffee in the area by far, and the cakes never disappoint.

The Scandinavian Benny and Frappé (Coffee)  that I got was AH-MAZING! I am a HUGE Benny fan, and my GOODNESS-- the best I have had. It's up there. Anyone curious-- just get it, enjoy it! There will be no regrets!
